SCALE UP INFRASTRUCTURE

INFRASTRUCTURE OVERVIEW:
User → HAProxy Cluster (LB1 + LB2) → Web Server → App Server → Database Server

ADDITIONAL ELEMENTS AND WHY:

1. ADDITIONAL SERVER:
   Added to split components onto dedicated servers.
   Each server handles one role: web, application, or database.
   Improves performance, security and scalability.

2. SECOND LOAD BALANCER (HAProxy Cluster):
   Two HAProxy load balancers configured as a cluster.
   Eliminates SPOF at load balancer level.
   If one load balancer fails, the other takes over automatically.

3. DEDICATED WEB SERVER (Nginx):
   Handles only HTTP/HTTPS requests and serves static files.
   Separated from app server to avoid resource competition.

4. DEDICATED APPLICATION SERVER:
   Handles only business logic and dynamic content processing.
   Can be scaled independently from web server.

5. DEDICATED DATABASE SERVER (MySQL):
   Handles only data storage and retrieval.
   Dedicated resources improve query performance.
   Easier to secure and backup independently.
